headline: Why This High-Yield Dividend King Has Plunged 25% and Why You Should Buy It Now
summary: Market uncertainty is high right now thanks to economic and geopolitical issues.  Consumer staples stocks have, on average, risen a couple of percentage points.  Generally speaking, consumer staples companies sell things that don't cost a lot of money, are effectively life necessities, and that get bought regularly.
